            width="800"
            height="500"
            loading="lazy"
          />
          <figcaption>Figure 3: Utilizing the PEEL paragraph structure 
          helps ensure that every body paragraph remains analytical, 
          evidence-based, and directly connected to your main 
          thesis.</figcaption>
        </figure>

        <h2>Concluding with Impact</h2>

        <p>The essay conclusion should tie all your arguments together 
        without introducing any new information. A solid conclusion 
        should:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Restate your thesis statement using different 
          phrasing.</li>
          <li>Summarize the main arguments presented in your body 
          paragraphs.</li>
          <li>Provide a final thought on the broader implications 
          of your research.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to Format an Essay for University</h2>

        <p>Proper presentation is essential for academic credibility. 
        Most universities deduct marks for poor formatting and 
        incorrect citations.</p>

        <table>
          <thead>
